value.value: Behavior related to the tendency of an organism to maintain internal equilibrium.
Behavior related to the deprivation of water.
Behavior related to the deprivation of food.
Behavior related to the drive of an organism to engage in sexual activity.
Any process which modulates the physical craving for food.
Any process which modulates the physical craving for food over short term food deprivation.
Any process which modulates the physical craving for food over long term food deprivation.

definition.value: "A pathological anxiety characterized by long-lasting anxiety that is not focused on any one object or situation." [wikipedia:Generalized_anxiety_disorder]

value.value: A pathological anxiety characterized by fear or anxiety triggered by a specific stimulus or situation.

definition.value: "A pathological anxiety characterized by brief attacks of intense terror and apprehension, often marked by trembling, shaking, confusion, dizziness, nausea, difficulty breathing." [wikipedia:Panic_disorder]

"A pathological anxiety primarily characterized by repetitive obsessions (distressing, persistent, and intrusive thoughts or images) and compulsions (urges to perform specific acts or rituals)." [wikipedia:Obsessive%E2%80%93compulsive_disorder]
"A pathological behavior characterized by one or more symptoms of a physical dysfunction but for which there is no identifiable organic cause." [wikipedia:Somatoform_disorder]
"A somatoform disorder characterised by a physical dysfunction (blindness, deafness, paralysis, numbness, etc. ) that has no underlying organic basis." [wikipedia:Conversion_disorder]

value.value: A somatoform disorder characterised by a continuing belief that one has one or more serious illnesses although no medical evidence supports the belief.

definition.value: "A mood disorder formerly characterised by alternating periods of mania and depression (and in some cases rapid cycling, mixed states, and psychotic symptoms)." [wikipedia:Bipolar_disorder]

value.value: Observable characteristic of behaviour related to cognitive processes.
Observable characteristic of behavior associated with the intake of food or liquids.

definition.value: Behaviors that are described for or done by groups of animals, not individual animals [NBO:SMAC]

value.value: A behavioral interaction between organisms in which one organism exhibits aggression using vocal or verbal means.
A discriminatory behavior that is related to age.
